The paper proposes solutions to improve the performance of federated learning, which is a popular topic in machine learning research. The proposed methods involve optimization algorithms and feature fusion, which are relevant to sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also discusses communication costs and convergence, which are relevant to sub-categories such as cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
